President Moon of South Korea welcomed President Trump to the Republic of Korea and expressed his hopes for peace on the Korean Peninsula. He emphasized the importance of continuous dialogue and denuclearization, and expressed his appreciation for the close alliance between South Korea and the United States. President Trump mentioned the progress that has been made in US-North Korea relations and expressed optimism for future talks. He also discussed the economic relationship between the US and South Korea. Both leaders mentioned their upcoming meeting with Chairman Kim Jong Un at the DMZ and expressed hope for progress in future negotiations.